- One year free admission to our museum, trails and regularly scheduled planetarium and live animal talks
- 10% discount on gift shop purchases
- Discounts on camps, workshops, and select special events (events and workshops with member discount will have special member tickets, member discount does not apply to all events and workshops)
- Free or discounted admission to more than 180 nature centers nationwide as part of the Association of Nature Centers Administrators Reciprocal Program. For a list of ANCA reciprocal sites, click

Residents
You already love nature and understand the impacts humans have on the world around them. That's why you live at Babcock Ranch. Now you can connect with nature outside your community with a
complimentary family membership to Calusa Nature Center and Planetarium
in Fort Myers! See the form below to claim your membership.
For over fifty years, Calusa has been educating both children and adults about our unique ecosystem and environmental issues concerning our area. We strive to provide a holistic environmental education program encompassing all areas from astronomy to ecology.
​
Our 105-acre site is home to many rescue animals, a butterfly garden, bird aviary, two nature trails, Southwest Florida's only planetarium, and much more!

Event Rentals
Iona House. Indoor rental space in natural environment in Lee County, Florida.
Iona House. Indoor rental space in natural environment in Lee County, Florida.
The Planetarium, seen from the stage, rentable for weddings, concerts, recitals, celebrations of life, etc.
Iona House. Indoor rental space in natural environment in Lee County, Florida.
1/11
Click on photo to view gallery
Hold your event in one of Florida's most unique venues. Indoor and outdoor spaces are available. Weddings, showers, meetings, and parties of all types are welcome.
Indoor event space includes Iona House, Natural History Museum, Planetarium, and Museum Classroom.
Outdoor event space includes Pine Pavilion with adjacent greenspace, Iona House meadow, Fire Circle, and McNew Pavilion under the museum.
For additional information check out our
Rental Venue Information Sheet
Rental Request Form
Please fill out the form below completely. Every event is "custom" so please understand, that we can't give estimates, dates, etc. until we receive this information. Please do not send other emails or call us, as it may delay the processing of your request. You will see a confirmation on the screen once you hit "submit." So, if you have submitted the form, know that we have received it.
We will get back to you as soon as it is possible. We have tremendous interest in our venue and answer each request in the order received. Thank you! We look forward to hearing from you.
